    <fr:title text="Neighborhood">Neighborhood</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topological space</fr:link> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> is a point on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, then a <html:strong>neighborhood</html:strong> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> is a subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> that includes an open set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> containing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>,<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[p\in  U\subseteq  V \subseteq  X.]]></fr:tex> This is equivvalent to the point <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p \in  X]]></fr:tex> belonging to the <fr:link href="/gtop-000H/" title="Interior" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000H/" display-uri="gtop-000H" type="local">topological interior</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
